<title>HONG KONG: Denway 1996 net loss HK$569.69 mln.</title>
<headline>Denway 1996 net loss HK$569.69 mln.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-05-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended December 31</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   43.2 loss   vs  17.7 loss</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    nil	   vs  nil</p>
<p>    Exceptional item	   272.85 loss vs  29.41 loss</p>
<p>    Net			    569.69 loss vs  233.05 loss</p>
<p>    Turnover		     712.67	vs  889.97</p>
<p>    Company name		 Denway Investment Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  N/A</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   N/A</p>
<p>Note - Denway is involved in automobile manufacturing and trading primarily through its holding in Guangzhou Peugeot .</p>
<p>Net is after an exceptional loss of HK$128.11 million on provision for doubtful debts, loss of HK$113.07 million on write-off of an intangible asset, loss of HK$17.22 million on write-off of obsolete fixed assets and loss of HK$14.46 million on write-off of an interest in non-consolidated subsidiary.</p>
<p>Total dividend for year is nil vs nil.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
